Citigroup Expects to Return Capital to Shareholders Next Year

-- B y   D o n a l   G r i f f i n
-- 
2011-10-17T13:43:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/citigroup-expects-to-return-capital-to-shareholders-next-year.html
Citigroup Inc. (C) , the third-biggest
U.S. bank by assets at midyear, affirmed its plan to buy back
shares or increase its dividend in 2012 after profit climbed in
the three months ended Sept. 30  “We’re confident that given the current economic
conditions, given our current condition of financial
strength, that we do expect to be in position next year to
return capital to shareholders,” John Gerspach, chief financial
officer of the New York-based bank, said on a conference call
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Donal Griffin in New York at 
